snippet: The Food and Drug Administration said Tuesday that it was investigating reports of nonviral hepatitis in Hawaii that has led to 11 hospitalizations and one death.
abstract: Food and Drug Administration says it is investigating reports of nonviral hepatitis in Hawaii that has led to 11 hospitalizations and one death; agency says link appears to be dietary supplement called OxyElite Pro, distributed by USP Labs of Dallas.
lead_paragraph: The Food and Drug Administration said Tuesday that it was investigating reports of nonviral hepatitis in Hawaii that has led to 11 hospitalizations and one death.
